section_1_excerpt: Identification SAFETY DATA SHEET Product name : SDS no. : Product use Disinfectant Spray Consumer use Uses : D8403873 Australia - 13 11 26 New Zealand - 0800 764 766 or 0800 POISON Poison Information contact: : Formulation # : FF151612AE–AU Supplier : AUSTRALIA RB (Hygiene Home) Australia Pty Ltd
section_2_excerpt: Hazard identification AEROSOLS - Category 1 SERIOUS EYE DAMAGE/EYE IRRITATION - Category 2A Classification of the substance or mixture : Signal word : DANGER Hazard statements : Extremely flammable aerosol. Pressurised container: may burst if heated. Causes serious eye irritation. Hazard pictograms : Precautionary statements Prevention : Keep away from heat, hot surfaces, sparks, open flames and other ignition sources. No smoking. Do not pierce or burn, even after use. Do not spray on an open flame or other ignition source. Wash hands thoroughly after handling. Response : IF IN EYES: Rinse cautiously with water for several minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present and easy to do. Continue rinsing. If eye irritation persists: Get medical advice or attention. Storage : Protect from sunlight. Do not expose to temperatures exceeding 50 °C/122 °F. Disposal : Not applicable. GHS label element
